    <text>
        <body>
        <div type="letter">
        <opener><dateline><date when="1918-04-26">April 26, 1918<dateline></date><salute>Dear <persName key="harriet_monroe">Harriet</persName>:</salute>
        </opener>
            <p>My friend, <persName key="florence_ayscough">Mrs. Francis Aysough</persName>, of <place key="shanghai">Shangai</place>, <place key="china">China</place>, is going to <place key="chicago">Chicago</place>. Her ostensible business is to sell a number of Chinese paintings which she has, and she will therefore be very grateful to you for giving her any introductions you can to the directors of the Art Museums or to private collectors.</p>
            <p>But entirely apart from her business, you will find her a most agreeable and attractive woman. She is a very old friend of mine. We knew each other when we were girls, and she knew your sister, Mrs. <persName key="lucy_monroe_calhoun">Calhoun</persName>, when she was in <place key="china">China</place>.</p>
            <p>I am sending her a letter to <persName key="mary_aldis">Mary Aldis</persName> at the same time I am sending this, and I need hardly say that any one else you can introduce her to who may give her the pleasure or help her to dispose of her collection will add very much to her stay. I envy you both. I wish I were going to be with you.</p>
            <closure>Affectionately yours,</closure>
        </div>
        </body>
    </text>
